<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,761,2010]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,761,786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[283,503,761,786]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pirhosigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcata">
<emphasis box="[283,503,761,786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">Pirhosigma sulcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from congeners by the following combination of features: male antennae with a reduced, triangular apical flagellomere, directed backwards above F 
<number box="[1002,1060,798,822]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
; pronotal carina developed along its entire dorsal margin; T 
<number box="[443,453,834,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="1.0">1</number>
with basal petiole extending further half of the tergum length; T 
<number box="[1172,1186,834,858]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="2.0">2</number>
without a basal dorsal hump; metasomal S 
<number box="[378,393,870,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="2.0">2</number>
smoothly convex. The species runs to couplet four of 
<bibRefCitation box="[1030,1307,869,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Giordani Soika, A. (1978) Revisione degli Eumenidi neotropicali appartenenti ai generi Eumenes Latr., Omicron (Sauss.), Pararhaphidoglossa Schulth. ed affini. Bolletino della Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia, 29, 1 - 420." type="journal article">
Giordani Soika´s (
<number box="[1241,1299,870,894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="1978.0">1978</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
key, better fitting 
<taxonomicName authority="Zavattari, 1912" authorityName="Zavattari" authorityYear="1912" box="[229,597,905,930]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pirhosigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mearimense">
<emphasis box="[229,243,906,929]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[260,395,906,929]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="118">mearimense</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zavattari" box="[412,588,905,930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" refString="Zavattari, E. (1912) Materialien fur eine Monographie der neotropischen Eumeniden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 78, 1 - 272." type="journal article" year="1912">
Zavattari, 
<number box="[531,588,906,930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="118" value="1912.0">1912</number>
</bibRefCitation>
